Blurb::
Define the vector with the inital point plus direction and magnitude of each step
Description::
The step vector defines the change in value for every variable, for a single step.
Step \f$n+1\f$ is step \f$n\f$ plus the step vector.

The points are determined by this step, plus the number of points.
